```javascript
import { h } from 'preact';
import { useState } from 'preact/hooks';

// Shared Tailwind CSS classes
const flexCenter = 'flex items-center';
const bgCard = 'bg-card p-2 rounded-md shadow-sm';
const textPrimary = 'text-primary';
const buttonDelete = 'text-destructive hover:text-destructive-foreground ml-2';

const TodoApp = () => {
  const [tasks, setTasks] = useState([
    { id: 1, text: 'Learn TailwindCSS', completed: false },
    { id: 2, text: 'Build a To-Do App', completed: false },
    { id: 3, text: 'Test Responsiveness', completed: false },
  ]);
  const [newTask, setNewTask] = useState('');

  const handleAddTask = (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    if (newTask.trim()) {
      setTasks([...tasks, { id: Date.now(), text: newTask, completed: false }]);
      setNewTask('');
    }
  };

  const handleDeleteTask = (taskId) => {
    setTasks(tasks.filter(task => task.id !== taskId));
  };

  const handleToggleTask = (taskId) => {
    setTasks(tasks.map(task => 
      task.id === taskId ? { ...task, completed: !task.completed } : task
    ));
  };

  return (
    <div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground flex flex-col items-center p-4">
      <div class="w-full max-w-md">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">To-Do List</h1>
        <form class="flex mb-4" onSubmit={handleAddTask}>
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Add a new task"
            class="flex-grow p-2 border border-input rounded-l-md bg-card text-card-foreground"
            value={newTask}
            onInput={(e) => setNewTask(e.target.value)}
          />
          <button
            type="submit"
            class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground p-2 rounded-r-md hover:bg-primary/80"
          >
            Add
          </button>
        </form>
        <ul class="space-y-2">
          {tasks.map(task => (
            <TaskItem
              key={task.id}
              task={task}
              onDelete={handleDeleteTask}
              onToggle={handleToggleTask}
            />
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

const TaskItem = ({ task, onDelete, onToggle }) => (
  <li class={`${flexCenter} ${bgCard}`}>
    <input
      type="checkbox"
      class={`form-checkbox ${textPrimary} mr-2`}
      checked={task.completed}
      onChange={() => onToggle(task.id)}
    />
    <span class={`flex-grow ${task.completed ? 'line-through' : ''}`}>
      {task.text}
    </span>
    <button
      class={buttonDelete}
      onClick={() => onDelete(task.id)}
    >
      Delete
    </button>
  </li>
);

export default TodoApp;
```

### Explanation:

1. **State Management**: We use `useState` to manage the list of tasks and the new task input.

2. **Task Operations**: 
   - `handleAddTask`: Adds a new task to the list.
   - `handleDeleteTask`: Deletes a task from the list.
   - `handleToggleTask`: Toggles the completion status of a task.

3. **Component Structure**:
   - `TodoApp`: Main component that holds the form and the list of tasks.
   - `TaskItem`: A sub-component that represents each task item. It handles its own delete and toggle operations.

4. **CSS Classes**: Shared Tailwind CSS classes are stored in constants to avoid repetition and make the code cleaner.

